---
import Layout from '../../Base.astro';
import SimpleHero from '../../components/SimpleHero.astro';
import FeaturedArticles from "../../components/FeaturedArticles.astro";
import ServicesRelatedWork from "../../components/ServicesRelatedWork.astro";
import "../../styles/pages/_services-list.scss";

---

<Layout
	title='Ongoing Retainers'
	description='Some businesses do not need one more one-off project. They need a reliable creative and digital partner who can keep work moving every week or every month.'
>
	<SimpleHero tagline='Ongoing Support Services' title='Ongoing Retainers' description="Some businesses do not need one more one-off project. They need a reliable creative and digital partner who can keep work moving every week or every month." lottieFile='ongoing-retainers.json' />
	<div class='service-body'>
		<div class='wrapper wrapper--narrow'>
			<h2>Where teams get stuck</h2>
			<p>After a launch or initial project, many businesses still need regular design, web, or marketing support. The work keeps coming, but the internal bandwidth is inconsistent and one-off projects slow everything down.</p>
			<p>That is usually when a retainer starts making more sense than starting from zero each time.</p>
			<h2>How we fix it</h2>
			<p>A retainer gives you structured access to Kelp so priorities can keep moving without rebuilding the relationship, scope, and process every few weeks.</p>
			<h2>Your options</h2>
			<h3 class="h6">Monthly Retainer</h3>
			<p>At the beginning of each month, Kelp is assigned a set number of production hours to accomplish the agreed upon tasks. This works well for teams that have a clearer roadmap and need reliable capacity to keep planned work moving.</p>
			<h3 class="h6">Weekly Retainer</h3>
			<p>These retainers are treated as weekly sprints where each week has a set number of production hours and a tighter feedback loop. They work best for fast-moving workloads that need consistent attention and regular prioritization.</p>
			<h2>What moving forward looks like</h2>
			<p>If your team needs a dependable partner to keep creative, web, or marketing work moving after the initial project, we can help recommend the cadence that fits the urgency and volume of the work.</p>
			<p><a href='/contact/' class='button button--green'>Plan Ongoing Support</a></p>
		</div>
		<ServicesRelatedWork tag={80} />
	</div>
	<FeaturedArticles />
</Layout>
